nal University, and the Vietnam Academy of Social Sciences</p><p>&#8211;  10 years as Coordinator of Living Values Education: Trained thousands of teachers in many provinces and cities in Vietnam through MOET and Plan International (UNICEF) projects on a student-centered approach focused on teaching the value of life.</p><p>&#8211;  5 years as a UNICEF specialist in psychosocial support for children committing crimes in Hanoi, Hai Phong, and Ho Chi Minh City</p><p>&#8211;  5 years as head of the psychology department with the task of psychological and behavioral support for street children at Blue Dragon Children (Australian NGO)</p><p>&#8211;  3 years as a school psychology consultant for Dinh Tien Hoang High School and Phuong Lien Secondary School</p><p>&#8211;  Visiting Lecturer for the Department of Psychology at the Marie Haps Institute, The University College, Léonard de Vinci, and the Department of Sociology at the University of Gdańsk, Poland</p><p>&#8211;  2 years as a leader of the project &#8220;Art in Community Development&#8221;</p>						</div>
