				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-dd010ab elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="dd010ab" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
							<p><strong>Qualification</strong>:</p><p>Master&#8217;s degree in Educational Science (Theory and Methods of Elementary Education) at Hanoi National University of Education</p><p><strong>Experience</strong>:</p><p>&#8211; Nearly 30 years of experience in Education: Academic leader, teacher, homeroom teacher</p><p>&#8211; Nearly 20 years of experience in studying modern and effective teaching methods, educational philosophy, and methodology; designing curriculum; writing High-school coursebooks, workbooks, and reference books, especially Math books; writing subject teaching plans; providing training on lesson plan design and teaching practices.</p><p><strong>Educational belief:</strong></p><p>High-level education brings students comprehensive PHYSICAL AND MENTAL development. The subject knowledge content delivered to students must be in line with the society in which they were born and raised. The school&#8217;s teaching method is the method of a modern school, accordingly, knowledge is considered as a product each student must create by themselves through a TASK system. Each of the TASKS entails a manipulating sequence with strict order that enables anyone to accomplish, then create their product with a minumum time amount. The golden rule of the school&#8217;s pedagogy is &#8216;not to give students ready-made products, but instead, they have to create the thing they need themselves&#8217;. Rather than compare one student with another, high-level education considers each student as an independent individual who is respected and can develop safely. The fundamental goal of high-level education is to enable students to solve real-life problems as much as possible, which benefits their ability to self-study and self-improve.</p>						</div>
